The paper discusses the efficacy of modern neuro-evolutionary strategies for continuous control optimization, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of suitable fitness functions and reward criteria, which is a topic related to reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the role of hyper-parameters, which is a topic related to robotics and control systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well.
